params.share: The amount of shares to add.
params.to: The address of the user to receive the assets.

params.share: The amount of shares to add for `to`.

returns.part: Total part of the debt held by borrowers.

params.to: Address of the receiver if `swapper` is zero.

params.fraction: The amount/fraction of assets held to remove.
params.to: The user that receives the removed assets.

returns.share: The amount of shares transferred to `to`.

params.to: Address of the user this payment should go.

accrue(uint256).notice: Accrues the interest on the borrowed tokens.

addAsset(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Adds assets to the lending pair.

addCollateral(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Adds `collateral` from msg.sender to the account `to`.

borrow(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Sender borrows `amount` and transfers it to `to`.

constructor.notice: The constructor is only used for the initial master contract. Subsequent clones are initialised via `init`.

liquidate(uint256,address,uint256,addres.notice: Handles the liquidation of users' balances, once the users' amount of collateral is too low.

removeAsset(uint256,address,uint256).notice: Removes an asset from msg.sender and transfers it to `to`.

removeCollateral(uint256,address,uint256.notice: Removes `share` amount of collateral and transfers it to `to`.

updateExchangeRate(uint256).notice: Gets the exchange rate. I.e how much collateral to buy 1e18 asset. This function is supposed to be invoked if needed because Oracle queries can be expensive.

documentation.text: @notice The constructor is only used for the initial master contract. Subsequent clones are initialised via `init`.
